title: Warning: Every element in a seq should have a unique :key:...
body: # Bug Report ## Problem It's very annoying to see the long warn log message `Warning: Every element in a seq should have a unique :key:...` while testing and trying to find your custom log information within `Metro(node)`. #### Expected behavior Don't print the long warn log message in `Metro(node)` after select `Join public chat` #### Actual behavior It will print the long warn log message in `Metro(node)` after select `Join public chat` ### Reproduction - Open a terminal and execute `cd status-react project root directory && make run-clojure` - Run an android emulator - Open another terminal and execute `cd status-react project root directory && make run-android` - Open Status - Press the add button - Select "Join public chat" - Then u will see the long warn message: `Warning: Every element in a seq should have a unique :key:...` ### Additional Information [comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.) - Status revision number: `63421631525192d637bcc0b580483f88839f811b` #### Logs [comment]: # (if on Android please replicate bug whilst running adb logcat) ``` [Mon Dec 28 2020 09:56:59.986] WARN Warning: Every element in a seq
